          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "1)Filter 2 keV. Filter components: 10B, Sc, S, 60Ni.",
                "The energy distribution center of this line is at 1.926",
                "keV; its relative intensity is 94.2% of the entire",
                "neutron flux. Besides, in the spectrum there are",
                "impurity lines: 6.039 keV(0.35%),7.448 keV(3.1%),27.59",
                "keV(0.35%), 42.816 keV (0.47%), 64.596 keV (1.31%) and",
                "a group of lines with energies less 300 eV (0.049%).",
                "2)Filter 59 keV. Filter components: 10B, V, S and 58Ni.",
                "The energy distribution center of this line is at",
                "58.735 keV; its relative intensity is 99.2% of the",
                "entire neutron flux. Besides, in the spectrum there are",
                "impurity lines: 36.101 keV(0.04%),345.663 keV(0.18%),",
                "367.674 keV(0.29%), 689.829 keV (0.13%), 783.644 keV",
                " (0.0161%), 1006.52 keV (0.001%),and a group of lines",
                "with energies less 300 eV (2e-7%).",
                "3)Filter 144 keV. Filter components: 10B, Si, Ti.",
                "The energy distribution center of this line is at",
                "144.485 keV; its relative intensity is 97.5% of the",
                "entire neutron flux. Besides, in the spectrum there are",
                "impurity lines: 35.420 keV(0.05%),53.899 keV(2.1%),and",
                "a group of lines with energies less 300 eV (0.12%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma rays emitted from the irradiated samples",
                "and the monitor foils were acquired with closed-end",
                "HPGe detector with sensitive volume of  110 cm3.",
                "Distance between detector cap and irradiated foil was",
                "equal 5 cm and fixed with centering device.  Energy and",
                "efficiency calibration of spectrometer was done with",
                "133Ba, 152Eu, 57Co, 60Co, 137Cs standard sources."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SPEC",
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Spectrometer with  Ge(Li) detector",
                "DGDK-32B was placed at the horizontal channel and used",
                "to determine the incident neutron flux using reaction",
                "10B(n,alpha+gamma)."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HE3SP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "Exposing the tantalic targets, simultaneously",
                "the monitoring of the neutron flux has been done by the",
                "neutron spectrometer with 3He-counter."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
